				<b><a href="javascript:openWindow(10,466197);"><font face="Verdana" size="1" >10</font></a></b>
				<font face="Verdana" size="1"><b>best</b></font>
			</td>
		</td>
		
	
	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I know most that come here are looking for the quick tip on getting the Phenocryst&#8217;s Focus. In fact I did that myself. All the information you need is in the previous posts. I enjoyed the quest so much I wrote a story that very closely follows the actual events of my quest for my Phenocryst&#8217;s Focus. It is a bit long but I hope some of you enjoy it. To those that made all those helpful, informative posts, this is my way of saying thanks!<BR>
<BR>
Bloodstar Deathshadow<BR>
56 Necromancer of Bristlebane<BR>
Chosen of The Nameless<BR>
<BR>
Searching for Focus<BR>
<BR>
Part I<BR>
<BR>
Thanks to the trusted Druid friend Linwen, Bloodstar now stands in the cold new region called Iceclad. It was bitter cold and the wind was howling. This was a far cry from the warmth of Burning Woods where Bloodstar seems to have taken up permanent residence.<BR>
<BR>
&#8220;I hope this is worth it&#8221; Bloodstar says with a scowl. Drawn here by rumors of a treasure called Phenocryst&#8217;s Focus, Bloodstar hoped to unlock some new dark powers.<BR>
<BR>
With Linwen his guide, he headed out for the fabled city of Thurgadin. A strange city of Dwarves that seem to be unaware of racial hatreds in other parts of Norrath. During the journey, which took them from Iceclad, through the Eastern Wastes, and across the Great Divide, Bloodstar saw many wondrous things. He of course would never admit to it though.<BR>
<BR>
The two entered Thurgadin at dusk. Linwen was a bit tired and decided to look for a tavern to have a few drinks and settle in for the evening. Bloodstar thanked him for his company on the trip and set out to find Normon Stonetooth.<BR>
<BR>
After asking around a bit Bloodstar headed to the mines to speak with Normon. Once he located Normon it became clear that Normon did not have all his marbles. You see, Normon likes to talk to the rocks&#8230; and they talk back to Normon. Bloodstar had no success in getting him to give up the information until he agreed to do a favor for Normon. He must take his pickaxe to Hakon and get it sharpened.<BR>
<BR>
Bloodstar finds Hakon quickly and ask for him to sharpen it. As Bloodstar waits he starts to wonder if he is loosing his own mind. &#8220;I can&#8217;t believe this! I am standing in a city of ice getting an axe sharpened for a dwarf that talks to rocks!&#8221;. Hakon hands the pickaxe back to Bloodstar and says with a grin, &#8220;their you go mister, you can run that back down to Normon now&#8221;. Bloodstar snatches the axe away from Hakon and mutters something about liking the dwarves that hang around Najena better.<BR>
<BR>
Once Bloodstar hands the pickaxe over, Normon is so happy he gives Bloodstar a Velium Focus. Normon tells Bloodstar he too can now listen to the rocks. On the way back with the pickaxe Bloodstar had decided he would kill Norman to make himself feel better about things. As he stood there now looking at the silly dwarf he could not see any point to it. He had gotten what he came for, and now it was time to visit Phenocryst.<BR>
<BR>
To find Phenocryst Bloodstar had to travel to the Wakening Lands. A place very much in contrast with everything else Bloodstar had seen since his arrival in Velious. The Wakening Lands were warm and full of life.<BR>
<BR>
Bloodstar took a deep breath, you could almost see a smile on his hard Dark Elf face. As he ran toward the cave where he hoped to find Phenocryst he saw something quite different. It was a dragon, he had heard their was a dragon in this area called Wuoshi. He moved a tiny bit closer to get a better look though the thick trees when he realized Wuoshi was coming to take a closer look at him.<BR>
<BR>
Bloodstar started to run as he cursed every God in Norrath. Soon he realized he could not out run this creature even with his trusty Journeyman Boots on. Some defense was in order. Wuoshi was now on him, he stopped cast a little used protection spell called Harmshield and stated to run again. Wuoshi was enraged as she tried in vain to rip the little Dark Elf to sunder. She could not break through that sickly green globe Bloodstar was surrounded in. As the power of the globe waned, Bloodstar decided to call on an old friend&#8230; Death.<BR>
<BR>
The green globe collapses, Wuoshi has now brought her full fury down on the Dark Elf. Bloodstar collapses, blood oozing from his body. Wuoshi laughs, &#8220;what a puny being, hardly any fun at all!&#8221;. Wuoshi heads back to her favorite spot, which is still in sight of where Bloodstar&#8217;s lifeless body lay.<BR>
<BR>
Occasionally Wuoshi looks over at the crumpled corpse and smiles. She notices some movement and to her horror that puny Dark Elf is up and running. Wuoshi roars, &#8220;You will not escape me Bloodstar!&#8221;. She sees that all to familiar green glow around him and decides to wait a bit. When the glow starts to fade Wuoshi begins to cast. She hits Bloodstar with a spell that racks his body with cold like nothing he has ever felt before. Bloodstar falls to the ground once again.<BR>
<BR>
Wuoshi stands over him, examines the corpse. &#8220;I got you for sure that time!&#8221; she says with an evil grin. Satisfied, she returns to her spot near the dragon circle.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Part II<BR>
<BR>
Bloodstar is hurt badly from the blast of cold. He lies on the ground, face down, shivering with blood coming out of is mouth and nose. He closes his eyes tight, concentrates, and tries to say the words. The words come, and once again Bloodstar feigns death. Darkness takes him, as he can no longer remain conscious. <BR>
<BR>
When he wakes, his body is numb and his head is pounding. He staggers to his feet as he starts to remember what happened to him. Realizing he is still in grave danger, Bloodstar forces himself to look for some shelter to tend to his wounds and clear his mind. He finds a cave close by that seems to be safe. Bloodstar starts a fire and pours some water on his head and face in an attempt to gather himself. He shakes his head and starts to meditate.<BR>
<BR>
Feeling somewhat restored, Bloodstar decides it is time to continue his quest. As he starts to search for the caves, he makes a mental note not to ever try to get a closer look at a dragon. Only a severe butt whipping will come of it.<BR>
<BR>
Without further distraction Bloodstar quickly finds the caves Phenocryst and the other Geonids call home. As Bloodstar enters the caves and sees the first of these Geonids he wonders how they will receive him. He does not have to wonder long because as he passes each one they seem to be indifferent to his presents.<BR>
<BR>
After searching though the caves Bloodstar finally finds Phenocryst. He tries in vain to speak to him, but there is no response. After a few moments, Phenocryst seems to communicate with Bloodstar mentally. He says, &#8220;we sense you are attempting communication with us but do not understand what it is you are trying to convey. We are eager to know more. Perhaps there is one who knows the language of the stone and will speak with us&#8221;.<BR>
Bloodstar remembers the Velium Focus that was given to him by Normon. He puts his hand on his forehead and says, &#8220;that crazed Dwarf said something about listening to the stone, maybe he was not so crazy after all&#8221;.<BR>
<BR>
Bloodstar hands the Velium Focus to Phenocryst. Phenocryst speaks to Bloodstar&#8217;s mind, 'you know the stone! This is wonderful! The fulfillment of the prophecy is now one step closer. The most ancient of the stone tells us that one not of stone will come forth and act as our harbinger of ascension. We believe you to be our harbinger. Please help us!'<BR>
<BR>
Bloodstar agrees to help and Phenocryst continues to speak without words, conveying a sense of joy empathically. 'It is said that the harbinger will find all of our people and unite them. When we join we will know all of our experiences and perhaps then be aware of how to proceed with the next step in our ascension. We implore you to find others like us and make them aware of us. You know the language of the stone and can tell them. We await your return with proof that you have spoken to them.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
The only other Geonids Bloodstar had ever heard talk of where in an area known as Crystal Caverns. This also meant another trip though the giant city of Kael Drakkal. Bloodstar like many others is not liked by the giants. He had barely made it though last time undetected. He hoped to use the same techniques to get through again.<BR>
<BR>
Standing just beyond the sight of the giant guards, Bloodstar calls on a spell that will make him invisible to the giants. This is a great spell but it does have a problem. Bloodstar has never been able to control it. It seems to quit working at the worst time.<BR>
<BR>
All invised up, Bloodstar starts his run through the city. Giants all around, the sweat starts to bead up on his forehead. Suddenly Bloodstar realizes he has taken a wrong turn. He is also barely aware of the blows that strike him down from an elite giant and his pet. Before he can do anything to protect himself his soul is wrenched from his body.<BR>
<BR>
Fortunately, The Nameless has plans for Bloodstar, which require him to be of the flesh. The Nameless contacts Walbort to reunite Bloodstar&#8217;s soul with his body. Walbort not wanting to question The Nameless gets to Kael as fast as possible to perform the ritual.<BR>
<BR>
Bloodstar is resurrected and his wounds are tended to. Memories of an incident in Hogcallers Inn come to Bloodstar&#8217;s mind as he tries to gather himself. &#8220;Maybe I have learned something of the Nameless today&#8221; Bloodstar says quietly.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Part III<BR>
<BR>
After taking a careful inventory Bloodstar decides he is ready to start his quest for this ancient magic item once again. He figures a visit to Crystal Caverns to search for more Geonids is the next step in his quest.<BR>
<BR>
The journey to Crystal Caverns is uneventful. Only stopping a few times to get his bearings and to kill a few unsuspecting giants to improve his mood. Bloodstar makes it to Ry'Gorr Keep in the eastern Wastes. The portal to Crystal Caverns is rumored to be here. Bloodstar searches but cannot find the portal. Alas, he runs into an ally from the guild Chain Unbroken.<BR>
<BR>
As Bloodstar continues his search in the main building he catches sight of a wolf. This turns out not to be your ordinary wolf, it is none other than Winegulper Whitebear, Druid from The Chain Unbroken. He runs up to Bloodstar and says, &#8220;Hello Bloodstar, are you here to kill these vile Orcs?&#8221; with an excited tone. &#8220;No, I am here to find the portal to the Crystal Caverns&#8221; Bloodstar says in response. Not unlike any male, Bloodstar does not like to admit he cannot find something. His Dark Elf blood will not allow him to be humble. Fortunately, Winegulper is familiar with Dark Elves and their hang-ups. He tells Bloodstar the portal is located in a hut south of the main building. Bloodstar then nods as a thank you gesture and heads to the hut.<BR>
<BR>
Once inside the Crystal Caverns Bloodstar pauses for a moment to look around and pull out his crude map. The map was hard to read, it was heavily stained with the blood of its previous owner. That owner did not want to part with the map and Bloodstar was not in a mood to negotiate. As Bloodstar squints to try and make sense of the bloodstained map he wonders if he should work on his negotiating skills.<BR>
<BR>
Bloodstar winds through the caverns for what seems to be an eternity until he finally finds a few of the rock creatures known as Geonids. He hands the Velium Focus to the first Geonids. The Geonid seems as if it doesn't recognize Bloodstar as anything of importance. Bloodstar attempts to speak with the Geonid through the velium focus but all he is able to hear is the same thought over and over, &#8220;Eat&#8221;. The Geonid hands the velium focus back. Disappointed, Bloodstar starts to put the focus back into the folds of his robe when he notices the focus as been changed slightly.<BR>
<BR>
As Bloodstar makes his way out of the Crystal Caverns he decides another visit to Phenocryst is in order. The journey is long but maybe he will know what to make of the change to the focus. Bloodstar, not used to traveling by foot, finds his mind wondering. He spends most of the trip back to the Wakening Lands trying to piece the puzzle together. The time passes quickly and Bloodstar is in front of Phenocryst before he realizes it.<BR>
<BR>
Bloodstar can since Phenocryst is excited by his return. Digging into the folds of his robe he finds the focus and hands it over to Phenocryst. Their minds seem to become one as Phenocryst makes his disappointment clear. 'It seems the others are not aware of themselves yet. We are alone. So many questions yet we can find no answers. We have been given a very special gift but without direction we are lost. We must find who has made us aware of ourselves and why it has done so.'<BR>
<BR>
Bloodstar is a bit confused by all this and makes it known he would like more information. Phenocryst says in the form of thoughts, 'we must call to it. We must make ourselves heard past these rocks. A Menhir must be constructed to amplify our voice. The stones we will need are not found in this area. We hear whispers of stones far away that have the ability to channel and amplify our thoughts. We ask you to gather these stones for us harbinger.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
Surprised by his own sadness, Bloodstar relates he is willing to help but he needs to know more about the stones. Phenocryst's thoughts flood his mind, 'Thank you Harbinger. We need 3 crystals. One of Beryl, one of Stibnite, and one of the purest iron. These minerals will only be found deep within the earth where the geology is relatively stable. This Focus will aid you in finding the right crystals. Return it to me with the 3 crystals and we will construct our Menhir. Please hurry Harbinger, our prophecy awaits.&#8221; Phenocryst then gives Bloodstar an Elbaite Focus. <BR>
<BR>
Bloodstar stands up, calls on the dark powers of Norrath. The spell brings him back to his home in Neriak. Holding the Elbaite Focus he slowly moves over to his desk. It had been some time since he had needed to do any research. He knew he would need to do plenty if he was to have any chance at finding the rocks Phenocryst required.<BR>
<BR>
As Bloodstar starts to pull out maps from his vast collection he wondered when he started to care. Perhaps the linking of minds with Phenocryst caused it. What started out as a quest for dark magic has become much more.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Part IV<BR>
<BR>
The research was extensive, after several days of non-stop work Bloodstar feels confident he can locate the rocks in three regions, The Burning Woods, Splitpaw, and The Great Divide.  He heads to the place he is most familiar with first, The Burning Woods. He travels down into a great meteor impact. The heat from the still smoldering meteor is almost unbearable. As he nears the meteor the Elbaite Focus starts to glow. Bloodstar now knows he is close to the crystal of purest iron. Shielding his eyes as best as he can he moves in closer. Through the waves of blistering heat he sees a shiny object jutting from the ground. Bloodstar wraps a piece of cloth around his hand and pulls the iron like crystal from the ground.<BR>
<BR>
Next stop is the home of the Splitpaw knolls. Bloodstar had respect for these knolls, they had moved in and killed their own weaker cousins. Bloodstar&#8217;s face bares an evil grin as he dismisses thoughts of trying that on his own kind. As he stands at the entrance to the caves that lead down into the lair of the Splitpaw, he decides it would be best to invis up and make a quick run to the target area.<BR>
<BR>
Once the spell completes only a wisp of smoke can be seen as Bloodstar heads into the cave. The cave is damp and the constant howling was enough to make Bloodstar pick up his pace, he did not want to be here long. He bolted through a set of double doors and was across the room before he could see the confused look on the dog like creatures that where to guard the entrance. A quick jump down though another set of doors and he was in the area he had come to check. One look at the focus and it was apparent he was in the right place. Bloodstar thinks of his Rogue friend Davian, &#8220;this stealth stuff is not so hard&#8221; he says to himself.<BR>
<BR>
With the benefit of the Elbaite Focus working as a guide the Beryl crystal is located quickly. As Bloodstar begins to softly speak the words to the spell that will take him out of the Splitpaw domain he becomes visible to the surrounding knolls. Once they get over the initial shock of seeing an intruder so deep within their home they charge. Bloodstar calmly displays a mocking smile as he completes the finale words of his spell.<BR>
<BR>
Once again Bloodstar finds himself in the inhospitable lands of Velious. Cursing the bitter cold he starts to make is way to the caves in the Great Divide. As he approaches the caves he spots a giant in the distance. Something inside him starts to churn. Before he knows it he is heading toward the giant with stone cold hatred in his eyes. Bloodstar pulls out some bones places them on the ground. He starts to cast a spell that will bring an unnatural being into the world to do his bidding, then he stops. &#8220;To fast, I want him to die slow&#8221; he whispers.<BR>
<BR>
Up through the snow the roots come, grasping the giant where he stands. His blood starts to boil as it carries poison through his veins. In a panic, the giant looks around to find the source of all his pain and terror. He does not have the look far to see the Necromancer slowly walking toward him, leaving the remnants of his dark magic swirling behind him. Bloodstar calmly sits down out of the giants reach and begins to tell the giant a story about a Necromancer that was attacked and killed in the giant city of Kael. Unfortunately for the giant, it was a long story.<BR>
<BR>
Feeling invigorated, Bloodstar invises up and heads into the cave. He passes several wurms as he searches the caves. Holding the Elbaite Focus in front of him as his guide he starts to home in on the last crystal. With the focus glowing strong Bloodstar makes his way into a large cavern. Two wurms appear to be staring at him even though Bloodstar knows that cannot be. A glimmer along side a patch of clear crystal catches his eye. Bloodstar quickly moves over to the crystal patch and recovers the stibnite crystal. Realizing he can now return and help the Geonids construct their Menhir he holds the crystal up and shouts, &#8220;the last crystal!&#8221;. This gets the attention of the two wurms who cannot see Bloodstar but now have a good idea of where he is. Bloodstar puts the stibnite crystal away and makes a hasty exit.<BR>
<BR>
Back in his home, sitting at his desk, Bloodstar contemplates the return to the Wakening Lands. He has decided the fate of the Geonids is too important to leave in only his hands. What if he where killed on the way? What if something comes while the Geonids where venerable as they made their Menhir? How could he alone protect them?<BR>
<BR>
He realized he would have to have help. Not just any help, the help of trusted friends.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Part V The Final Chapter<BR>
<BR>
After careful consideration Bloodstar is able to assemble a group of experts in the art of warfare.<BR>
<BR>
Anvel &#8211; Warrior<BR>
Muttz &#8211; Warrior<BR>
Nulbus &#8211; Warrior<BR>
Yaratomo &#8211; Ranger<BR>
Aenorn &#8211; Rogue<BR>
Trail &#8211; Druid<BR>
Linwen &#8211; Druid<BR>
Qelinya &#8211; Wizard<BR>
Lavlin &#8211; Wizard<BR>
Nadana &#8211; Cleric<BR>
Krystl &#8211; Cleric<BR>
<BR>
This was the group Bloodstar felt had the best chance to protect him on his journey back to the Geonids. They would also be a formidable force to protect the Geonids should they be attacked has they make the Menhir.<BR>
<BR>
The trip through the giant city of Kael was a bloody one. Several giants took exception to the intrusion. The battles where hard fought, but in the end the team showed their metal and emerged into The Wakening Lands bruised but not beaten. After some attention was given to the wounds the party moved on toward their objective, the Geonid caves.<BR>
<BR>
Standing at the mouth of the cave Bloodstar pulls out is map. The caves twist and turn, it is almost impossible to navigate even with a map. Bloodstar runs through the caves, but soon becomes lost. Once again his arrogant dark elf nature takes over and he continues to search the caves rather than ask for assistance or admit he is lost. Through sheer luck Bloodstar finally finds Phenocryst. He then pulls all the crystals out of his robes along with the Elbaite Focus and hands them over to Phenocryst.<BR>
<BR>
Phenocryst makes no sound but his voice fills Bloodstar&#8217;s mind. 'We have always held our memories within the earth and stone but only recently have we become aware of them. We do not know what happened or who gave us this wonderful gift but we can now access those memories and are aware of its storage. With that knowledge has come questions and desires. When the prophecy comes to be then we will have our answers and fulfill our desires.'<BR>
<BR>
Phenocryst 's familiar thoughts flood into Bloodstar&#8217;s mind again, 'you truly are the Harbinger, take this Focus as a mark of your friendship with us. Now we can construct the Menhir, we need&#8230; the stones speak&#8230; there is a problem. Ones of flesh are coming, the large ones, three of them. They must not disturb us while we construct the Menhir! Please stop them Harbinger! Bring us proof of their destruction along with your Focus and then we will begin the calling. Our ascension is at hand!'<BR>
<BR>
Bloodstar looks into his hands and sees the Azurite Focus, glowing dimly. He starts to head out of the cave, then remembers he is lost. Bloodstar knows this is no time for pride, he calls out to Linwen the Druid. Once Bloodstar calls for Linwen he stands still and waits for his friend to arrive. You see, Linwen is an excellent tracker but he gets very upset if you keep moving around as he is tracking to you.<BR>
<BR>
Linwen arrives quickly, he and Bloodstar exit the caves. Once outside Bloodstar hands the Azurite Focus over to Linwen and tells him to use it to locate the &#8220;large ones&#8221;. Linwen darts out with the spirit of the wolf in him. Using his own tracking abilities and the Azurite Focus he finds a giant that is charging toward the caves.<BR>
<BR>
Linwen casts a druidic spell on the giant. The giant forgets about his mission and now wants to crush the little druid. Linwen must use all his speed and agility to stay ahead of the rampaging giant. As Linwen darts through the underbrush of the Wakening lands the giant is right behind him laying waste to anything in his path.<BR>
<BR>
Heart pounding, Linwen makes his way to the group. Somewhat breathless with his hands on his knees announces, &#8220;giant&#8230; coming&#8230;&#8221;. The group of seasoned veterans quickly and efficiently gather their items as they prepare for the battle. Anvel swings his two massive swords through the air in a mock display, &#8220;finally I get to hack on something&#8221; he says as he tries to see the giant through the thick trees. Anvel and the rest of the group did not have to wait long. The giant crashes into the camp, looks at all the little ones and starts to laugh, &#8220;You puny beings are no match for me!&#8221;. The intense battle seemed to last forever, but in fact it was over quickly.<BR>
<BR>
No cheers, no words where spoken. Victory is expected among this group. Aenorn pulls out a cloth and starts to clean his daggers. The large Barbarian Anvel raises his arms and mutters something toward the heavens, unaware of the blood running down his face and chest. The casters all sit down and meditate in unison like a bard song. The group runs like a fine instrument awaiting its next note. <BR>
<BR>
Once again Linwen enters the camp abruptly, out of breath &#8220;one.. more.. big guy..&#8221;. The second giant storms into the camp, he sees his fallen brother, &#8220;you insects will pay for killing my brother!&#8221; he shouts. With that the fight is on. Everything is going very much the way the first fight went, fast, and efficient. Then Linwen returns with another giant, but this one is different. He is known as the Bloodpriest, and he begins to heal his son. Once the Bloodpriest is done with his healing, he turns to Linwen and slams his fist down on the little Druid. Linwen lays still on the ground, he is hurt but not dead. The Bloodpriest sees that he is still alive and cast upon Linwen to finish him. Linwen is now hurt badly, he softly speaks the healing words that restore his health.<BR>
<BR>
While the Bloodpriest was focused on Linwen, the group was able to finish off the other giant. Now they brought there full fury down on the Bloodpriest. The battle raged, as the group would bring the Bloodpriest close to death he would call to his god and be fully restored. The group becomes weary as their resources are almost fully drained. The Bloodpriest starts to heal again when Qelinya and Lavlin decide they had seen enough. They glance at each other and nod. The two Wizards call on their most powerful magic. The Bloodpriest, still trying to complete his spell freezes in mid sentence. His eyes seem to stare at nothing as blood starts to flow from his eyes, nose, and mouth. He drops to his knees and falls to the ground.<BR>
<BR>
Bloodstar looks around at the party, he can sense relief but not surprise. As the group goes through their post battle routine Bloodstar gathers the medallions from the giants and heads into the caves. This time making sure he heads in the right direction.<BR>
<BR>
Once he locates Phenocryst, he hands him the Azurite Focus and the three medallions. Phenocryst 's thoughts become his, a feeling of joy overwhelms Bloodstar, 'Because of you we can at last speak with our maker. We were once given a gift, and we ask that you accept this gift from us now so that we may come closer to that which we owe our sentience to. Now..,we must construct the Menhir..'<BR>
<BR>
Bloodstar looks at the gift as it pulsates with a red glow. Somehow he thought he would be more excited to receive such a gift. This will allow him to improve his dark magic, but it also means his quest has come to an end.<BR>
<BR>
Phenocryst begins to resonate. The stones around him start to resonate at his command. The Geonids all begin moving to construct the Menhir. Bloodstar follows the Geonids out of the cave. He stands in awe as a giant Geonid is constructed from all the Geonids. Once the single giant sized Geonid is complete it looks over at the group as if to say thank you, then turns its massive head toward the heavens and starts to resonate. Tiny cracks appear along the Geonids form with light blazing outward. The light becomes brighter as the cracks become larger. Suddenly there is a hug explosion. Bloodstar is not sure if the Geonids made their ascension or not. He also realizes he does not care either. Now convinced Phenocryst had some mind control over him Bloodstar was glad to see them go.<BR>
<BR>
Back in his home in the Third Gate of Neriak, Bloodstar stared at the gift he was given which he had appropriately named the Phenocryst Focus. Its pulsating red glow was almost hypnotic. &#8220;It will take some time to unlock your secrets&#8221;, he said softly. He then laid down on his bed and closed his eyes. Thoughts of dark powers swirled in his head as he lay there with an evil grin creeping across his face.<BR>
<BR>
The End
