			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				At first, it might seem like if you have killed enough geos to lower your faction, you have no chance of completing the quest. there is however, a nice little way to get your faction up if you aren't yet to the point where they will attack you outright. I was apprehensive, and gave him the focus, and got some message about how I could feel sadness and dissapointment, coming from the empathy of the geonids yadayada. this happened, and I couldn't believe it. I had spent 30 mintues of my time on this quest and now it was all wasted gone, just cause I had killed 2 or 3 geos back in the day. that was my thinking at first. I was so disapointed, I just sat down right there in front of the pheno guy and logged for a couple of hours. and guess what I realized when I logged back on. I realized (more like remembered) that now 10 seconds from when you zone into a zone, you are indifferent to every mob. soo... if you are apprehensive (like me), you just get your focus, sit down and camp, and when you log back in, immediately give him the focus, and it will act as though you are indifferent and will actually work. doing this one time I went to indifferent from appre, and I did it again for good measure, and went from indiff to amiable. bascailly each time you do this (this meaning giving him the focus you got from the pickaxe guy), you go up one faction shot. so, one could technically still get their pheno focus even if they are dubious to the geos, it'll just be annoying running back and forth to thurg and pheno each time. <BR>
oh, and now I have a question. after giving the focus ot a geonid in CC and giving it back to pheno, I then said &quot;I will gather these stones for you&quot;. in fact, I said this and several variations (&quot;will help you gather&quot;, &quot;gather the stone&quot;, &quot;gather the stones&quot;, etc) and for some reason he never responded or gave me the elbait focus. is it because the quest is somehow broken, or because I did the first part more than once that it wont work for me, or do I have to say both things twice in a row, or what? just wondering if other people had any ideas... :)
				</font>
			</td>

