	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Here's a quick summary.  I've done this twice now (once for a wizzie friend, once for myself).<BR>
<BR>
- Get a TPing friend and pick up all the items.  When I got mine (before they moved the Paw one) they seemed to repop every 1-2 hours.<BR>
<BR>
- Do the faction part even if you're a chanter.  Better safe than sorry, and it'll make traveling in the caves easier.<BR>
<BR>
- When you turn in the 4 crystals, after about 4 mins the 2 Accolyte's will pop.  Usually straight out from the cave, a little to the right.  Get your tracker out there (fully buffed) to pull them quickly as the zone mobs will kill them.  We never pulled additional mobs.<BR>
<BR>
- Best to either charm one (Bard is best since the charm breaks fast and chanter wouls waste mana) or kite one (you can't snare, so just run back and forth along the wall with SOW not JBoots).  Buff all you've got on the kiter and puller.<BR>
<BR>
- The Bloodpriest will find his way to you.  Sometimes a minute or so after you kill the Accolytes, sometimes during or immediately after.  With a good group he'll only CH once.<BR>
<BR>
- Mobs all seem to be magic resistant, but not at all fire resistant.  If you have a high level shammie or mage, use the Malo line to help the others.<BR>
<BR>
- Best group has a couple 52+ melee and/or 54+ mages (pets and DD).  You need one tracker (52+ druid, ranger, or good bard).  You need a healer (52+ shammie or cleric, shammie can also slow).  And a wizzie for good measure is always nice (also wizzies and druids are good at kiting, so they can kite the second accolyte).<BR>
<BR>
- My group had a 52 tank, 56 mage, 56 wizzie, 54 shammie, 55 mage, and 54 druid.  Was pretty easy to take all the giants out.<BR>
<BR>
- Make sure to OOC/SHOUT to zone that you are doing the quest!  The first time we did this some other group killed the blood priest and looted the amulet.  My wizzie friend had to get all the pick-up items again since this can't be multi-quested.<BR>
<BR>
- Pheno and geonid train dance out of the cave, and create the super geonid.  Yellow to me at 56.  Supposedly the pheno repops in about an hour, so if you have multiple folks, best to turn in the crystals multiple times then let the INT casters turn in the medallions later (don't need a group for that).<BR>
<BR>
- Looks like a GBS when wielded, looks like a quartz crystal in inventory, acts as a light source too.<BR>
<BR>
Now I have a GBS, Pheno, and Drachnid Thyxl.  What to do with all three???<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
